originalText.text: I graduated from JFK HS in 1988. I feel that this school is judged by its negatives, and not judged by what it  offers. When I went we had Drafting, Automotive, Superior Math and Science Classes the Best Sports Department Hands down. I can happily say that I am a product of this Amazing school. If you don't feel the same, then transfer somewhere else. But believe it when I say, its a Great school, It has shaped me to become the Man I am today!

originalText.text: I was the first class to graduate from Kennedy High School in 1975. Those High School years were the best years of my life. I went on to college and worked in the medical field until I retired. It's sad to hear the negative comments. I will always hold my sweet memories close to my heart...

originalText.text: I took my SATs at this school and this is the high school my younger sister attended. It is absolutely horrible. My sister did not get enough help preparing for college and she ended up missing a semester (i.e. she had to wait till January to enroll, instead of going straight to college after high school). The students are horrible. You got these pretentious thugs that make you wanna commit murder and the staff are as useful as a towel under water. NEVER ENROLL YOUR KID IN THIS SCHOOL!
